Author: jl777c#5810
Content: we are currently stress testing a single nSPV full node with 850 superlite clients bombarding it at fullspeed. so far it seems to be holding up pretty well, so we get almost a 1000x capacity of nSPV clients, which means the existing ~1000 fullnodes would be able to support a million nSPV clients. I got most all the validation working, so the proper data is indeed going from the fullnode to the superlite client and allowing it to validate the segment of blockchain using dPoW. it literally takes 2 seconds to startup, login and spend funds, even on KMD chain. that is even for first use
